reviews.text: Stopped by on a whim. Very glad we did.  It was all amazing.  I had the Tama Samoa with the 'regular' style fries with the Passion Orange Guava drink. Best.... Food..... Ever...... others in my group also had the loaded fries, Seek's Deep Blue, Shez's Paniolo Burger, and the other special refresher drink flavors.  All compliments to the food.

Delicious burgers!!! I got the Spencer burger and it was sooooo good! They have a great kids menu here with perfect portion size. My husband loves the crazy fries. He said the Shem burger is very good but messy to eat! The employees are all very nice and have great service. The restaurant feels a tad small, but there‚Äôs a good amount of tables. We looove Seven Brothers!

The burger was fantastic! I was craving a good quality burger üçî and a friend suggested we go here. I had never been but was very pleased with quality of all of the ingredients and their sliced potatoe fries were very good and crispy! Highly recommend this spot

Seven Brothers Burgers is a solid pick for Utahians craving hearty, flavorful, Hawaiian‚Äëtwist burgers with indulgent toppings. The Paniolo burger and fries are standouts. Desserts like the banana‚Äëbread sundae are surprisingly delightful. While prices lean on the higher side and quality may vary a bit by location, the delicious, creative menu and warm, fast service earn it strong recommendation.

This is an amazing location!  The food was great, and the service was too!  I wasn‚Äôt expecting much with the vegetarian sandwich but it was amazing!! I loved all of the sauce with the delicious pineapple mushrooms and avocado.  I would definitely get it again. And there is something magical about the fries. SO good and crisp. My family also loved their spencer and max burgers. We appreciated the server coming to our table and asking if we needed any more sauce or napkins towards the end of our meal.

It was my first time at Seven Brothers.
I had the Shem burger and the Paniola fries. These fries, even the small portion which I had are delicious and a meal in itself.
My burger was also delicious. The guacamole on it had just enough spice to add a tasty zing. If this had not been a first time for me I would have asked for the bacon to be a little more crispy. Nevertheless the portion was generous and very flavorful.
I will certainly try other menu items in future visits.

detailedReviews.author: Craig Blackwell
detailedReviews.text:
Our second time eating here and a complete letdown.  My daughter ordered the crispy chicken sandwhich.  The chicken patty was thinner than a beef patty and 90% of it was the hard breaded coating she couldn't finish it.  She banged it on the table. We paid $2.00 extr for avocado which was the equivalent to a smear of avocado paste from a butter knife.  Rip off.  Not to mention they forgot her order when they brought our other two.  My wife ordered the sterling which had a lot of onions on it.  The menu doesn't list onions and they upset her stomach. They put the onions under the cheese  and she  lost all the cheese in effort to remove the onions.  She ate about 4 bites and couldnt finish it as she said the whole thing was too sugary sweet.  She called it a candy burger.
The only good thing we had were the fries. We looked three times after the food came and never saw anything about the onions.  It's OK, we won't be back.

detailedReviews.text: Seven brothers is our families favorite burger joint. Hayden who was taking orders was legit. One of the best dudes. Helped me decide what to get. Place was clean and food was awesome! Highly recommend if you are looking for somewhere to eat.

detailedReviews.author: Allison Cherrington
detailedReviews.text: I came to Seven Brothers today and my taste buds are still sending me thank you notes. The place was pretty busy, probably because everyone knows how good it is. Hayden took my order and honestly deserves a gold star. He was super friendly and didn‚Äôt judge me for how hangry I looked. My burger was so good I almost cried tears of joy. The bun was so soft and perfect I wanted to write it a love poem. Everything tasted fresh, like it had been blessed by burger angels. You can tell they really care about their food here. Hayden made the whole visit even better ‚Äì give that man a raise!

detailedReviews.author: Joel Marion
detailedReviews.text: Seven Brothers nails it every time - but this time it was peak. Hayden and the staff here brought it & went above and beyond. The floors were a little greasy, but when you‚Äôre frying burgers like these ones, it happens.

detailedReviews.author: Amanda N
detailedReviews.text:
As I walked towards the place I was thinking, "Please don't be anything like 5 guys". They obliged.

The food was too plentiful, and delicious. I got the Spencer, which has jalapenos, bacon, etc. It was very good. The onion ring had to come off the burger or I'd never have managed to get the sandwich in my mouth. Halfway through the burger, I thought, "I can't really taste the burger with all this other goodness on it." So I pulled out a chunk of just the meat. That's a burger that could stand on it's own. Yum, baby, yum!

I also got a small order of crazy fries. If there are two of you, still probably get the small. I didn't even make it through half of them. But I liked that they brought them out before the burger.

The staff all seemed amazing. The girl who took my order was delightful and knew her stuff. There was a young man whose way I kept getting into, and he was very swet about it. And then there's Hayden. When he brought out my burger, I had questions. Hayden had answers. He knows about the family behind the food, he knows about the food. But smiles and enthusiasm abound with this young man. He seems to be quite proud of working here. (As a matter of fact, all the staff seemed happy to be here.) I hope Hayden's boss knows what s fantastic employee he's got in Hayden.

And clean. While I was eating, one of the guys came out and wiped down tables. And seats. Then Hayden came and gathered trash of the floor from all the kids that had just left. Then someone swept.

I will definitely be back - and I'll be looking for y'all when I go to Hawaii next May.

detailedReviews.text: Great time! Great people! We‚Äôll be back!!!

detailedReviews.text: The cashier was amazing. Didn‚Äôt catch her name but long brown hair and just so kind and helpful.. The shrimp surf/turf was so so good! Yummy! I‚Äôm going to be dreaming of that shrimp!
